<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 04 at 5:21AM CDT  by NWS QuadCities</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Henry
and southwestern Bureau Counties through 600 AM CDT...
At 520 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Kewanee, moving northeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Sheffield and Buda around 540 AM CDT.
Other locations in the path of this storm include Wyanet.
This includes Interstate 80 in Illinois between mile markers 39 and
48.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
